<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - TROUBLESHOOTING - VOLTMETER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>VOLTMETER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08207x_17.xml" xrefid="x0820712">VOLTMETER</hotlnk>
            for operation description of the voltmeter.
        </para>
        <table id="t0820724" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Voltmeter Circuits From Speedometer/Tachometer Module To Gauge Cluster (Mechanical And
                Electronic Engine)
            </title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.48in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.62in"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove connector (422) from Speedometer/Tachometer module and remove connector (424)
                                from the gauge cluster. At connector (424) measure resistance to ground at circuits
                                27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and 27C(-).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(424), 27S, and 27C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K ohms, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (424) measure resistance between circuits 27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and
                                27C(-) and between all other circuits in the connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(424), 27S and 27C and all other circuits.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short between any circuits with less than 100K ohms resistance between
                                terminals, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance of circuits 27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and 27C(-) between connectors
                                (422) and (424).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(424) and (422), 27S and 27C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in any circuit having more than 5 ohms resistance, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove voltmeter. At gauge cluster side of connector (424) measure resistance between
                                terminals 9, 10, 11, 12.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(424), term. 9, 10, 11, 12.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (424) terminals 9, 10, 11, 12 and the
                                corresponding gauge terminal connections in the cluster.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(424), term. 9, 10, 11, 12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>The circuits between the Speedometer/Tachometer module and voltmeter cluster terminals
                                check good. If this test was performed after steps in Gauge Circuit Troubleshooting,
                                replace the Speedometer/Tachometer module. If not, perform steps in
                                <hotlnk document="s08207x_40.xml" xrefid="x0820708">GAUGE CIRCUIT
                                    TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
